Kogi State Governor, Yahaya Bello, has approved the appointment of ten new Permanent Secretaries in the state public service. The Punch reports that in a statement signed by the Head of Civil Service, Kogi State, Mrs. Hannah Odiyo, stated that the newly appointed officers would replace those who recently retired from the civil service. The statement explained that the appointments were based on merit, hence must be seen as a call to service. -Advertisement- The HoS enjoined the new appointees to live above board and continue to remain loyal to the administration in the course of their duties. According to the statement, those appointed as approved by the governor are Obadaki Zainab David – Adavi; Yakubu Dele Musa – Ankpa1; Andi Modupe Stella Maris – ljumu; Audu Alami – Idah, and Idoko Enejoh Celestine – lgala-Mela Odolu. Others are Moraiyewa Adeniyi Mathew – Kabba/Bunu; Isah Hussaini Sule – Kogi; Adegbola Isaiah Toluwa – Ogori/Magongo; Ajodo Benjamin Ike – Ibaji, and Razak Falilat – Yagba East.